PN,36704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1772806277
OL,3,CHow MP Naz Shah overcame 'toughest
OL,4,Cbeginnings' to represent her community
OL,6,F"I didn't know anything was going on",
OL,7,Fshe tells me, "I didn't know she was
OL,8,Fbeing sexually abused or exploited
OL,9,Flike she was."
OL,11,F"Needing that home security, that roof
OL,12,Fover her head, that was the thing that
OL,13,Fkept her in that position to suffer
OL,14,Fthat abuse and not talk about it, not
OL,15,Fseek any help.
OL,17,F"She suffered for years until she came
OL,18,Fto the point where she thought she had
OL,19,Fno other way out."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1772806277
OL,3,CHow MP Naz Shah overcame 'toughest
OL,4,Cbeginnings' to represent her community
OL,6,FNaz's mum feared Azam would turn on
OL,7,Fher children, and decided to take
OL,8,Fdrastic action. In 1992 she killed him
OL,9,Fwith poison and was sentenced to
OL,10,Ftwenty years in prison.
OL,12,FNaz remembers the first time she saw
OL,13,Fher inside saying it was like "leaving
OL,14,Fa kid in nursery for the first time
OL,15,Fwhen they look back at you and say
OL,16,Fplease don't leave me here".
OL,18,FNaz says she is "very mindful that
OL,19,Fsomebody lost a father, lost a
OL,20,Fhusband... and that's not right for
OL,21,Fthat family."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1772806277
OL,3,CHow MP Naz Shah overcame 'toughest
OL,4,Cbeginnings' to represent her community
OL,6,FBut she adds: "This was a person who
OL,7,Fbehaved like a monster towards my
OL,8,Fmother and my mother felt she didn't
OL,9,Fhave any other choice but to do what
OL,10,Fshe did."
OL,12,FZoora did not speak about the abuse
OL,13,Fshe had endured during her trial.
OL,14,FHowever, when it emerged Naz and her
OL,15,Ffamily fought for her sentence to be
OL,16,Freduced, which it eventually was in
OL,17,F2000.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,368,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1772806277
OL,3,CHow MP Naz Shah overcame 'toughest
OL,4,Cbeginnings' to represent her community
OL,6,FShe says "as much as for us this was a
OL,7,Fpersonal fight for our mother, this
OL,8,Fwas much more than our mother. This
OL,9,Fwas about how women are treated in
OL,10,Fsociety".
OL,12,FNaz says that her experiences allow
OL,13,Fher to relate to her constituents'
OL,14,Fconcerns.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
